                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Essential Skills Every PC User Should Have]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/essential-skills-every-pc-user-should-have/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/vintage-desktop-pc-with-floppy-drive-keyboard-and-mouse-in-neon-lightning.jpg" length="371" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The fist steps to PC independence.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>So you want to be a PC user that doesn't have to rely on IT support for every little thing? You want to deal with most issues on your own, and feel in control of your computer?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:15:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/essential-skills-every-pc-user-should-have/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[watchOS 26 Is Now Coming To An Apple Watch Near You]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/watchos-26-is-now-coming-to-an-apple-watch-near-you/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/apple-wwdc25-watchos-26-hero-250609.jpg" length="356" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[watchOS]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Less glass than on your iPhone, that's for certain.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>iOS 26, macOS 26, and iPadOS 26 are all here. But watchOS 26 is perhaps one of the most overlooked. Apple has just released its latest watch update, and like its cousins in other hardware, it’s very packed.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:10:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/watchos-26-is-now-coming-to-an-apple-watch-near-you/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[iOS 26 Is Finally Out With a Ton Of New Features]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ios-26-is-finally-out-with-a-ton-of-new-features/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/apple-wwdc25-ios-26-hero-250609.jpg" length="467" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's glassy, but that's not the only thing it has going for it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><span style="font-size:11pt; font-variant:normal; white-space:pre-wrap"><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif"><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="text-decoration:none">It’s been a long time coming. iOS 26 has been in the works for a long time, and it’s one of the wildest iOS updates we’ve seen in a long time. Now, it’s finally here—and it’s packing a heck of a lot of changes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:06:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ios-26-is-finally-out-with-a-ton-of-new-features/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Pixel's Scam Detection Is About to Get Even Better]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pixels-scam-detection-is-about-to-get-even-better/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/a-phone-call-with-google-scam-call-detection.jpg" length="837" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Stopping junk in its tracks across all your apps. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you wish your Google Pixel's scam detection feature worked in more places, like your favorite chat apps or Instagram Messenger? If so, we have some potentially good news. This week, we learned that Google is getting ready to expand this great feature beyond calls and texts, making its phones safer than ever.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:54:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pixels-scam-detection-is-about-to-get-even-better/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[New York Wants to Restrict TikTok, YouTube, and Instagram]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-york-wants-to-restrict-tiktok-youtube-and-instagram/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/tiktok-logo-on-black-screen.jpg" length="129" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Social Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[instagram]]></category><category><![CDATA[YouTube]]></category><category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category><category><![CDATA[TikTok]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The latest age verification law to be proposed in the United States.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>New York is moving forward with a law that could force major social media platforms like TikTok, YouTube, and Instagram to roll out some form of age verification before minors can access their highly personalized, algorithm-driven feeds.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:47:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-york-wants-to-restrict-tiktok-youtube-and-instagram/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This NZXT Tenkeyless Gaming Keyboard Is 58% Off Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-nzxt-tenkeyless-gaming-keyboard-is-58-off-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/nzxt-function-2-minitkl-keyboard-in-front-of-box.jpg" length="213" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Keyboards]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            More than half off for a reliable keyboard.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You can get the NZXT Function 2 MiniTKL keyboard for a major 58% discount. This drops the price to a surprisingly low <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CST2HK9G?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2016572&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fthis-nzxt-tenkeyless-gaming-keyboard-is-58-off-today%2F&asc_campaign=Affiliate" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$55 on Amazon</a> from its usual $130. This is a massive discount on a high-quality gaming keyboard that comes from a big name like NZXT.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:29:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-nzxt-tenkeyless-gaming-keyboard-is-58-off-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Add Desktop Windowing to Your iPad With iPadOS 26, Available Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ipados-26-available-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Andrew Heinzman]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/4.jpg" length="1318" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPad]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPadOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The update supports iPad models going back to 2018.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The iPadOS 26 update is now available for all eligible devices. This update, which is most notable for its desktop-like functionality and "Liquid Glass" redesign, is arguably one of the biggest iPad updates that we've seen since 2020.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:15:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ipados-26-available-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Which Macs Are Compatible With macOS 26 Tahoe?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/macos-tahoe-is-now-available/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Andrew Heinzman]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/macos-26-tahoe-logo.png" length="4000" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The new update sheds support for seven Intel Macs.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The macOS 26 "Tahoe" update is now available. Defined by its "Liquid Glass" theming and improved Spotlight search, macOS Tahoe is one of the more notable updates in recent memory, and it's the last major update for Intel Macs.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:14:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/macos-tahoe-is-now-available/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Laptop Webcam Cover Might Break Your Screen]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-laptop-webcam-cover-might-break-your-screen/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_1435078217.jpg" length="278" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The price or privacy?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you're aware of modern cybersecurity issues, then you're probably someone who wants a privacy cover on their webcam. There's nothing wrong with that in principle, but in some specific cases this could lead to serious hardware damage to your laptop screen.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-laptop-webcam-cover-might-break-your-screen/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How I Stay Focused and Fit at My Desk Job]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-stay-focused-and-fit-at-my-desk-job/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aran Folsom]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/smiling-woman-working-on-a-laptop-with-floating-icons-of-do-not-disturb-dumbbell-pomodoro-timer-and-stopwatch.png" length="2395" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Fitness]]></category><category><![CDATA[health]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't let your desk job keep you stationary.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Like many desk jockeys, as we're less than affectionately called, staying fit in a sedentary line of work can quickly become a task all on its own. Coupled with the difficulties of maintaining focus in a boring office environment or while working from home like me, it doesn't take much to become overwhelmed in this seemingly easygoing lifestyle.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 16:31:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-i-stay-focused-and-fit-at-my-desk-job/</guid></item></channel>
